Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Software Engineer* role with *Upstart*. I bring over three years of professional experience building full-stack web applications, distributed systems, and AI-powered experiences, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade systems that directly reflect the technical depth the Borrower Experience team demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I designed and delivered an MCP AI interaction layer integrating agentic and LLM-powered capabilities across 1,000+ platform endpoints — translating natural-language intents into safe, validated tool calls to enable end-to-end self-service customer actions. I architected the underlying concurrent multi-agent orchestration system using LangChain and LangGraph, with full observability via LangSmith covering tracing, structured logging, and evaluation hooks across distributed systems. To drive continuous improvement, I applied A/B testing and experimentation to optimize prompt routing, cutting end-to-end latency by 60% and LLM API costs by 50% — the same analytics-driven mindset Upstart's BX team applies to improve payment success and reduce borrower friction. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I contributed to an Identity & Access Management platform built with React, Spring Boot, and AWS supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications, and developed AWS Step Functions workflows to orchestrate long-running data import jobs across microservices — improving payment pipeline reliability and preventing Lambda timeouts. These roles have prepared me to design and deliver full-stack borrower-facing features, contribute to architectural decisions that unify systems into a cohesive experience, and drive measurable improvements in self-service outcomes.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in AI model development and technical communication — skills that translate directly into the engineering discipline and collaborative culture Upstart values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I managed the full model development lifecycle for StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion research, from training on Pace's HPC cluster to inference optimization with vLLM, with reliability and explainability as first-class concerns. I also led workshops on GPU programming and AI Agents for 50+ students — an experience that sharpened my ability to communicate complex technical concepts clearly across teams, mirroring the cross-functional partnership with Product, Design, and Analytics that this role requires.

I have always been passionate about expanding access to affordable credit and using AI to make financial systems fairer for all Americans, and I am energized by Upstart's mission to radically reduce the cost and complexity of borrowing. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration — I look forward to connecting!

